5 (d) Provide proof of the contractor's registration under this section to an
6 insured and the insured's insurer with any authorization of a direction of
7 payment under a property, casualty, or property and casualty insurance
8 claim; and
9 (e) Comply with:
10 1. Subsection (4) of this section; and
11 2. KRS 367.620 to 367.628.
12 (4) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, in order to protect
13 the safety and well-being of first responders, victims of the declared state of
14 emergency, and others in the designated area, a contractor shall not solicit
15 business in person within the designated area for ninety (90) days after the
16 state of emergency was declared without prior approval of the property
17 owner.
18 (b) This subsection shall not prohibit:
19 1. A contractor from soliciting business in person upon the request of the
20 property owner;
21 2. Public advertising; or
22 3. Direct communications by telephone or digital means.
23 (5) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, a local government
24 shall not require any emergency registration or emergency licensure for a
25 contractor that complies with subsection (3)(a), (b), and (c) of this section
26 during the period of time determined by the Attorney General under
27 subsection (2)(a) of this section.
